rComments: A lifesaver! If you feel stressed throughout the course, go talk to him.

He is very clear on what he expects of you. In his final review, there r small hints as to what will show up. Lab exercises are very helpful to properly understanding the material. He can get tough in marking at the beginning but he's very fair and caring guy. He is very smart and wants you to succeed. Honestly, the best prof I've ever had.

Dr. Mohammad is a strong CS prof. His lectures are very well-detailed. He also put a lot of effort preparing synchronous office hours that showed off sample questions and answered student questions. Although the course is a bit difficult for someone with zero coding background, he provides sufficient resources for you to pass with flying colours!

Prof Alnabhan is honestly one of the best profs I've had. Very simple and straightforward guy. As long as you go to class and labs, you will do very well. Most of his exam questions are simple and straightforward, and if you study you will get an A. Content is also pretty interesting.

Amazing professor! Really cares about students and puts in more work that is required of him to help as many students as he can succeed. 

If you didn't get a reasonable grade, it was on you. He was more than fair.

You can tell Prof. Alnabhan is a very passionate about CS and he really wants you to succeed, but his teaching methods are so dry and confusing at times, and if you have no coding background you will literally be forced to learn from other sources. I am sure he will be successful in the IT industry but I don't see that as a professor.
